place.name: STURSTON
place.gazetteerText: STURSTON, a parish in Thetford district, Norfolk: 4½ miles SSW of Watton r. station. Post town, Thetford. Acres, 2,000. Real property, £904. Pop., 75. Houses, 10. The living is a p. curacy in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £28. Patron, Lord Walsingham. There is no church. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
